Whatever happens, all this uncertainty is giving
retailers pricing-strategy d=C3=A9j=C3=A0 vu, as they must again decide whe=
ther to absorb higher costs, or pass them on to shoppers. Many brands took =
advantage of last month=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9Cpause=E2=80=9D on Canadian and M=
exican import tariffs by moving extra merchandise into U.S. warehouses. But=
 with China seeing tariff stacking just one month after the initial hit, an=
d April whispering ominously of another encore, it=E2=80=99s time for retai=
lers to sharpen those pricing pencils. =E2=80=94Sarah Shapiro

